HEADWORD: Yellowwort
<hw>Yel"low*wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A European yellow-flowered, gentianaceous (<spn>Chlora
perfoliata</spn>). The whole plant is intensely bitter, and is sometimes
used as a tonic, and also in dyeing yellow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

